    "2) Graphs of social networks: These networks are helpful research tools for identifying trends in the collective behavior of individuals, groups, and organizations.",
    "We may create a graph that represents groupings of people by visualizing individuals as nodes and their connections as edges [63].",
    "3) Citation networks as graphs: When they publish papers, scientists regularly reference the work of other scientists.",
    "Each manuscript can be visualized as a node in a graph of these citation networks, with each directed edge denoting a citation from one publication to another.",
